\ul \ulc0 UK Crime Data Analysis Project
\f1\b0 \ulnone \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Exploratory Analysis of UK Crime Data for Real Estate Decision Support\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa321\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \ul Project Overview\ulnone \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 This project analyses crime patterns across selected regions of the United Kingdom using publicly available crime data from the UK Police open data portal. The aim of the project is to explore how crime levels vary across different policing environments and to identify insights that may be relevant for real estate sales and investment decisions.\
The analysis was conducted for Nadine Green, Head of Sales, who is interested in understanding which locations may be more or less desirable from a property market perspective. Crime levels can influence neighbourhood perception, buyer confidence, and long-term property value, making crime analysis a useful input when evaluating property markets.\
The project follows a structured data analysis workflow consisting of:\
